node MLR · MLR · ⟦Willam Black:MLR:fb73f7⟧

WHO   — Willam Black — the sailboat seeker
WHAT  — The heart of the page: the dumb-bastard everyman who only wants to see the thing everyone insists is right there — and finally does.
WHERE — MLR · Mallrats (1995)  Framework inputs: Mallrats (1995, dir. Kevin Smith, Gramercy/View Askew); verified cast & facts  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because the film's gentlest gag is also its truest — the human ache to finally see what you've been told is obvious.
HOW   — By staring, losing the schooner-versus-sailboat argument to a child, melting down, and at the very end — seeing it.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  It's not a schooner, it's a sailboat! …there is no Easter Bunny! …oh. Oh — SAILBOAT! I finally see the sailboat!

